<p><a name="Theatre_Festival" id="Theatre_Festival"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Abbie_Hoffman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Theatre Festival">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Theatre Festival</span></h2>
<p>The Mary-Archie Theatre Company in Chicago started the "Abbie Hoffman Died For Our Sins" Theatre Festival in 1988. This festival runs every year for 3 consecutive days as a celebration of the Woodstock Music and Art Fair of 1969. <a href="http://www.maryarrchie.com/abbie.html" class="external text" title="http://www.maryarrchie.com/abbie.html" rel="nofollow">Festival website</a></p>
